<h1>Mabuhay! Welcome to the Philippines</h1>
<h3>It's more fun in the Philippines</h3>
<p>Look no further for a place to relax and unwind</p>
<ol>
<li>Enjoy the idyllic beaches of Bohol. With more than 12 beaches on the tiny island of Bohol, there is enough sand for everyone. From the <b>White Beach</b> on the west side of the island to the <b>Puka Shell Beach</b> on the northern tip of the island full of unique and collectable shells to <b>Cagban Beach</b> with nearby caves rumoured to contain treasure chests, you are sure to find the right one for you. </li>
<div style="text-align: center;">
    <img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:3600/1*PEjHSVUw2ckOj9Zt00xRpw.jpeg" alt="Bohol Beach" height="300" width="500">
</div><p></p>

<li>Discover the Chocolate Hills of Bohol. This UNESCO protected site is a collection of over 1200 geologocial formations that turn brown in the dry season, resembling a landscape of chocolate herseys kisses. </li>
<img src ="https://www.travelandleisure.com/thmb/Uyi3xc1u5Z3hUbSGSDqaJMoOV9s=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/chocolate-hills-PHIL0116-3a853dd3c6704d84bb5162bb37404279.jpg" alt = "The Chocolate Hills" height="300" width="500" class="center"><p></p>

<li>See the Banaue Rice Terraces which were carved into the mountainside more than 2000 years ago. 1500 meters above sea level and spanning 4000 square miles, these terraces provide much of the rice for the surrounding areas and if each step of the terraces were laid end to end, they would reach over 12,500 miles</li>
<img src ="https://byunique.com/gallery/?album=1904&width=1024" alt = "The Banaue Rice Terraces" height="300" width="500" class="center"><p></p>

<li>Navigate the Subterranean River of Palawan stretching over 5 miles. If that doesnt tickle your fancy you can explore the rock islands, caves and natural parks of the island </li>
<img src ="https://media.cntraveler.com/photos/5668630dc3c9e01555a4d421/master/pass/palawan-philippines-coron-cr-alamy.jpg" alt = "Palawan" height="300" width="500" class="center"><p></p>

<li>Manila is the perfect blend of History, Modern, Culture, Cuisine and Nightlife</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>History - Explore the 15th Century Manila at Intramuros in a traditional horse carriage</li>
<img src ="https://www.travel-palawan.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/manila-city-tour-copy.jpeg" alt = "Intramuros" height="300" width="500" class="center">
<li>Modern - See the ultra modern Bonifacio Global City nestled into the heart of Manila with its towering buildings, high end shops and excellent night markets</li>
<img src ="https://d1hjkbq40fs2x4.cloudfront.net/2019-10-02/files/1569984365.jpg" alt = "BGC" height="300" width="500" class="center">
<li>Culture - Take a ride on the unique transportation found in the Philippines. Jeeneys are the most popular transportation around the city. Converted WWII trucks are found everywhere and drivers are encouraged to express their personality through the the way they paint the exteriors </li>
<img src ="https://thediplomat.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/sizes/td-story-s-2/thediplomat_2024-01-01-195835.jpg" alt = "Jeepney" height="300" width="500" class="center">
<li>Cuisine - Whether you have adobo, bangus, balut or lumpia, no Philippine meal is complete without Halo-Halo and ube ice cream</li>
<img src ="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/60e46c6701084801b06de2a3/1:1/w_2560%2Cc_limit/Halo-Halo-Recipe-2021.jpg" alt = "Halo Halo" height="300" width="500" class="center">
<li>Nightlife - Manila is a 24 hour city and never stops. You will always find a hive of activity no matter what time you venture outside</li>
<img src ="https://static.tripzilla.com/thumb/a/4/184484_800x.jpg" alt = "nightlife" height="300" width="500" class="center">

</ul>


</body>
